<title type="html"><![CDATA[What mapper should I use for my game (if any?)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4793&amp;p=42468#p42468"><![CDATA[
It looks like you could go with CNROM (CHR-ROM) or UNROM (CHR-RAM). Those are some of the simplest boards there are, meaning they are easy to reproduce. The MMC1 has been cloned by bunnyboy, but discrete logic (CNROM, UNROM) is much simpler, and probably enough for your project.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu Jan 29, 2009 7:27 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
