<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4793&amp;p=42461#p42461</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4793&amp;p=42461#p42461"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[What mapper should I use for my game (if any?)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4793&amp;p=42461#p42461"><![CDATA[
For cutscenes, you'd definitely want to have CHR-ROM so that you can have cutscene tiles on the top of the screen and text tiles on the bottom or something like that.<br /><br />Mapper 3 would do if you just want more graphics. If you run out of PRG space, you'd want to switch to either mapper 2 or mapper 1.<br /><br />Also, by "one-screen" game do you mean you have only one screen shown at a time or that it requires one-screen mirroring ? Because only mappers 1 and 7 (among with much less common mappers) allow one-screen mirroring officially.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Thu Jan 29, 2009 2:48 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
