<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4793&amp;p=42452#p42452</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4793&amp;p=42452#p42452"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[What mapper should I use for my game (if any?)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4793&amp;p=42452#p42452"><![CDATA[
Perhaps you'd want to go with MMC1, and about 16k of CHR ROM. It's possible movies would take up a bit of space, so if you need to use more than 32k of PRG you could move up to 64k, which would give you the specs of Dragon Warrior. But I think 64k is kind of a waste if you're not going to use it all.<br /><br />I'd suggest trying to have 32k of PRG and 16k of CHR ROM. It doesn't seem like you'd benefit much from CHR RAM with a small project, and if you don't feel limited by it, CHR ROM is much easier to deal with.<br /><br />Look at this list of games/mappers:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://tuxnes.sourceforge.net/nesmapper.txt">http://tuxnes.sourceforge.net/nesmapper.txt</a><!-- m --><br /><br />It might be outdated, but I don't know. You may find it helpful in choosing a mapper.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=138">Celius</a> — Wed Jan 28, 2009 10:06 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
