<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4793&amp;p=42450#p42450"><![CDATA[
Hello,<br /><br />I'm designing a one-screen game and I'm trying to decide what mapper to use, if any.  I don't think my game will need extra PRG-ROM at all, so really it comes down to CHR.<br /><br />My game isn't complex.  It will have a title-screen with a picture and text, a main gameplay screen with a relatively static background, credits.  Sounds like Mapper 0 (no mapper) is the way to go so far... but!<br /><br />But I want to have little cut scenes in between levels to tell the story.  Something like <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=4520" class="postlink">the intro that Roth has for his zombie game</a>, but with more text.  　I think it will require more background tiles than a single page of CHR-ROM will give me.　　If I understand correctly, I need a Mapper to get more CHR space. (correct me if I am wrong!)<br /><br />So switchable CHR-ROM or writable CHR-RAM?  I was thinking about using UNROM (CHR-RAM), but only because that's the mapper I am most familiar with (and it looks extremely easy to use).  Do you think this is a good choice?  If not, why not.<br /><br />One last thing: I'd like to put my game on a cart (possibly several) when I finish, so I want to make sure I pick a mapper that will make this as painless as possible.<br /><br />Which mapper would you choose?<br /><br />Thanks a lot! <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3632">MetalSlime</a> — Wed Jan 28, 2009 9:44 pm</p><hr />
